      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To verify guardrails and planks are safe, inspect the top rail for continuous integrity, ensure it is securely bolted to the standards, and check that the toe boards are firmly attached. Run your hands along the planks to feel for any rot, splintering, or loose nails, and confirm that the spacing between them is uniform and that they lie flat without significant gaps. If you see any cracks, warping, or missing fasteners, replace or repair them immediately before the crew steps on the structure.",
